tip.text: If you have a timing to go do your hair, do call Didie for appointment or even walk-in. Been there twice, but Didie not around. So had to wait til she's in again. Pricings & Contact no. on photo.
Great infinity pool. But no lifeguard, maybe on a wkday noon. No one else were there. So swim safely.
I'm not a coffee addict but...I really like the coffee I had from that bottle. Said to be mixed of Johor & Pinang. Will come here again, instead of Starbucks if in Malacca.  ☕️
Satisfied 1st visit. Will come again. Delicious Laksa! We bought the paste & crispy chili too. Delicious & spicy Asam Pedas in claypot! 👍🏼👍🏼 Very nice coffee too!
Check on your table for wifi password (1st line) & their social media name & hashtags. Or don't be shy, just ask them for it. Hehe.
Was recommended to this place. And yes the Cheese Naan is delicious & soft. Tandoori taste good together. We even tried the Fish Masala & it is very delicious too. As photo, total up to RM46.
Won't mind coming here again BUT not during peak period. Because we have to eye for our own table & shamelessly wait beside the table we want. Can't eat in peace somehow with a lot of people eyeing.
